        <p>Zen Tech's revenue for the quarter stood at <strong>‚Çπ141.52 crore</strong>, which was a 44% increase from ‚Çπ98.08 crore in the same quarter last year. However, on a sequential basis, revenue declined by <strong>41%</strong>, down from ‚Çπ241.69 crore in the previous quarter. The revenue shortfall was primarily due to delays in shipments and the company's decision to push revenue recognition to Q4 FY25. These issues led to concerns among investors regarding the company‚Äôs execution and its ability to meet market expectations.</p>

